gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: C
task: C3
title: "fix(diagrams): BOM list does not scroll to selected part on hotspot click (#1374)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P3
refs:
  - CROP-front#1374
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, REACT_SERVER_COMPONENTS, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  Clicking a hotspot on a parts diagram should scroll the BOM list to the
  corresponding part row. Currently the list does not respond — the user has
  to manually find the part in the list. Fix: on hotspot click, scroll the
  BOM list container to the matching row using scrollIntoView or equivalent.

scope:
  in:
    - Diagram hotspot click handler — trigger scroll to BOM row
    - BOM list row — add id or ref anchor for scroll target
    - Smooth scroll preferred; instant acceptable if smooth causes jank
    - Manual verify: click hotspot → BOM row is visible without manual scrolling
  out:
    - Changing the diagram rendering or BOM data shape
    - Any other diagram interactions

acceptance:
  - Hotspot click scrolls BOM list to the matching part row
  - Works on mobile viewport (touch + scroll)
  - No layout shift or double-scroll artifacts

dep: none
output: diagram hotspot handler + BOM list row scroll anchor patched
